## 5. `SalesPointController`

**Location:** Arthur Core
**Class:** `SalesPointController`

Make cookie optional and handle expired session cleanly:

```java
@GetMapping
public ModelAndView salesPoints(
        @CookieValue(value = "ARTHUR_SESSION", required = false) String sessionId
) {
    if (sessionId == null || sessionId.isBlank()) {
        return new ModelAndView("redirect:/auth/login-expired");
    }

    UserSession session = redisSessionService.findBySessionId(sessionId);

    if (session == null) {
        return new ModelAndView("redirect:/auth/login-expired");
    }

    ModelAndView mv = new ModelAndView("views/sales-points");
    mv.addObject("salesPoints", session.getSalesPoints());

    return mv;
}
```

For POST:

```java
@PostMapping("/select")
public void selectSalesPoint(
        @CookieValue(value = "ARTHUR_SESSION", required = false) String sessionId,
        @RequestParam String salesPointId,
        HttpServletResponse response
) throws IOException {

    if (sessionId == null || sessionId.isBlank()) {
        response.sendRedirect("/arthur-core/auth/login-expired");
        return;
    }

    String redirectUrl = authService.completeSalesPointSelection(sessionId, salesPointId);
    response.sendRedirect(redirectUrl);
}
```

